 10  # Equivalence relations
 11  
 12  The first section of the file defines the complete lattice of equivalence relations
 13  on a type, results about the inductively defined equivalence closure of a binary relation,
 14  and the analogues of some isomorphism theorems for quotients of arbitrary types.
 15  
 16  The second section comprises properties of equivalence relations viewed as partitions.
 17  
 18  ## Implementation notes
 19  
 20  The function `rel` and lemmas ending in ' make it easier to talk about different
 21  equivalence relations on the same type.
 22  
 23  The complete lattice instance for equivalence relations could have been defined by lifting
 24  the Galois insertion of equivalence relations on α into binary relations on α, and then using
 25  `complete_lattice.copy` to define a complete lattice instance with more appropriate
 26  definitional equalities (a similar example is `filter.lattice.complete_lattice` in
 27  `order/filter/basic.lean`). This does not save space, however, and is less clear.
 28  
 29  Partitions are not defined as a separate structure here; users are encouraged to
 30  reason about them using the existing `setoid` and its infrastructure.
 31  
 32  ## Tags
